    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Receptacles, usually metal or terracotta, having a base designed to hold live coals, and sometimes with a grate or pierced top, used for heating a room or for heating or cooking food.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
